QA: 14hr IN: 10, AC: 2, PD: 2

EI to change XP to allow ACA to run through a 2nd time when ACA exhausted the first time.

[https://support.transporeon.com/servicedesk/customer/portal/1/DEVSERVICE-51544]

 

When the ACA is executed for the second time, it should run through all the valid carriers who service that lane just like the first time it went through.  Regardless if the carrier has declined on the first round, we will tender it back to them again on the second round.  After the second round, the transport should be moved back to To Do for further action by Dreyer's.  But it should not run ACA in a loop more than 2 times.

comments.body: {-}Description is missing{-}. You need to present the Efforts in the standardized way.

I've tested with multiple transports, many of them resulting on an error while searching for rates. I'm not sure if the error is expected, but I will need some clarification on this behavior, if it is correct  or if I need to do some workaround. Transport number is LA002_28038.

Log ID: 3869df54-bf77-caa2-5d3b-df725ad83a16

 

!image-2025-04-06-23-37-57-811.png!

Hi [~dominguez@transporeon.com] can you please share some sample txns so [~vinicius.fava@transporeon.com] can start testing in INT. Thanks in advance

Btw I have tested with transport TL002_8519 number following below steps
 * import a new transport which will trigger ACA -> transport gets routed to specific carrier 
 * decline transport at carrier side -> tour.rejected event is processed, ACA is triggered twice  

Is this what we are expecting after the changes?

I am trying to review the order number used for testing - and I cannot open the transport.  It gives me the error below.

 

!image-2025-04-07-09-33-30-365.png!

I declined the transport TL002_8519 again to see what it will do.  It looks like it is in a loop.  They only want to run the ACA one more time after all carriers have declined the first time.  This transport looks like it keeps going back to ACA to tender to the same carriers more than twice?

 

!image-2025-04-07-09-39-44-216.png!

[~dominguez@transporeon.com]  so when ACA is executed for the second time, should we still filter out those carriers that declined the transport? If so, second ACA will still have the same outcome as the first one, it will be exhausted as the first ACA because as nothing has changed, correct?

[~jenisse.vereau@transporeon.com]  - Hi Elizabeth.  When the ACA is executed for the second time, it should run through all the valid carriers who service that lane just like the first time it went through.  Regardless if the carrier has declined on the first round, we will tender it back to them again on the second round.  After the second round, the transport should be moved back to To Do for further action by Dreyer's.  But it should not run ACA in a loop more than 2 times.  Is this clear?  If not, please chat with me on message DM.

hi [~dominguez@transporeon.com] 

can you please let me know if below test case will be valid

*precondition*
 # carriers A, B, C available
 # import transport
 # aca at import
 # routed to carrier A 

*steps* 
 # carrier A declined
 # routed to B via ACA, declined by B
 # routed to C via ACA, declined by C
 # *ACA executed but no carriers found, 2 ACA execution considering A, B, C happens*
 # routed to A via 2 ACA, declined by B
 # routed to B via ACA, declined by B
 # routed to C via ACA, declined by C
 # *ACA executed but no carriers found, transport moved to TODO  (2 ACA should not be triggered)*
 # transport routed to A via ACA, declined by A
 # routed to B via ACA, declined by B
 # routed to C via ACA, declined by C
 # *ACA executed but no carriers found, transport moved to TODO  (2 ACA should not be triggered?)*

 

We have already discussed regarding 8 , but what about 12 ?  should transport behave as it is a new brand transport after ACA exhausted in the first round ? should we trigger 2 ACA attempt or just move it to TODO?

Hello [~jenisse.vereau@transporeon.com] 

This is how I see the transport moving through ACA - - see below.  It should only run once for the second time and if no carrier accepts, move it to To Do.

*steps* 
 # carrier A declined
 # routed to B via ACA, declined by B or allowed the transport to expire
 # routed to C via ACA, declined by C or allowed the transport to expire
 # *ACA executed but no carriers found, 2 ACA execution considering A, B, C happens*
 # routed to A via 2 ACA, declined by *A or allowed the transport to expire*
 # routed to B via ACA, declined by B or allowed the transport to expire
 # routed to C via ACA, declined by C or allowed the transport to expire
 # *ACA executed but no carriers found, transport moved to TODO  (2 ACA should not be triggered)*
 # *STOP*

Hi [~dominguez@transporeon.com] I see some setup was added regarding exchange standard interface, this configuration is conflicting with code changes for ACA. This configuration is not set for prod and test envs. Can you please take a look, not sure if this will resolved the requirements and no code changes will be needed. Let me know thanks

 

!image-2025-04-11-13-47-28-491.png!

[~jenisse.vereau@transporeon.com] we needed this setting for ACA to go to the next carrier. Without this it would go back in To Do. If we take this out your code will need to handle sending it to the next carrier. Are you okay with that?

Hi [~kevin.nguyen@transporeon.com] [~dominguez@transporeon.com] 

can you please take a look at TL012_0000 

Steps to reproduce scenario
 * transport was imported,
 * ACA executed, got routed to ESNL,
 * ESNL declined,
 * ACA executed, no carriers found,
 * second ACA executed considering ESNL again,
 * routed to ESNL,
 * ESNL declined, moved to TODO

from now on every time transport gets declined or expired ACA will just be ran once
I reviewed the test file TL012_0000 and it looks like it worked as expected.  Can this be moved to ACC?  On Monday?

(/) working as expected, transport do not run ACA in a loop more than 2 times.

*Example:-*
* Transport No. TL022_0000
hi [~dominguez@transporeon.com]  we can move to AC as testing has been complete, I will need a UR ticket created. let me know
Hi [~jenisse.vereau@transporeon.com]. Thank you for making the change. Here's the request. [https://support.transporeon.com/servicedesk/customer/portal/1/DEVSERVICE-55619]
